Class ConditionalValue

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.gembox.spreadsheet.conditionalformatting.ConditionalValue

    public final class ConditionalValue
extends Object
implements com.gembox.internal.core.Equatable<ConditionalValue>
    Represents a conditional value used in conditional formatting rules which format all cells based on their values (ColorScaleCondition, DataBarCondition and IconSetCondition).
    See Also:
    Excel Conditional Formatting example

      • getValue

        public Object getValue()
        Gets the value.

        Value is

        • equal to null if getValueType() is equal to ConditionalValueType.NONE, ConditionalValueType.AUTOMATIC, ConditionalValueType.LOWEST or ConditionalValueType.HIGHEST.
        • double if getValueType() is equal to ConditionalValueType.NUMBER, ConditionalValueType.PERCENT or ConditionalValueType.PERCENTILE.
        • String if getValueType() is equal to ConditionalValueType.FORMULA.
        Returns:
        The value.
